<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Muse, I really hope you aren't jumping on the 'kick Verant for making the game better' bandwagon. A good video card with 16M of ram can be found for under $50 on the net. Memory costs are tumbling as well. I find it hard to believe that people would spend $50 on a game (and $10 an month) and then balk at paying $50 on a video card so they can play it properly. <P>EQ is almost unique in the realm of compuoter gaming in that it has lasted so long. Any other long-lived piece of software regularly goes through regular revisions which inevitably require a hardware upgrade. It is perhaps slightly unfortunate that all users of EQ are forced to upgrade, but that's the nature of the beast. Verant's decision to make DirectX 7 the new baseline is entirely logical and appropriate.
</FONT>
