Before this gets off track, just wanted to comment on the last two posts.  I'm not griping about the change.  I'm simply interested in what people think is a reasonable upgrade to these persistent games.  Should they have required 128 MB of RAM and totally redone the engine instead, thereby making sure they're top of the line for the duration of their game?  Yes, I sometimes gripe about this stuff, but I'm genuinely curious what people think of this stuff, especially in light of the problems that ensued for many people, both with having to upgrade and also the compatibility issues.<P>------------------<BR>Muse<BR>Bard and Cartographer
