My current system is P200 MMX using DSL. I had to upgrade RAM when my son wanted to strart playing EQ, the video had already been upgraded.  I also started playing EQ when the new version of Baldur's Gate would not run on my computer.  <P>I think the fact that EQ still works on this now almost four year old system says a lot for the hardware design. No new game will work. At the same time, the pace of hardware advancements is such that a game can't remain static in its hardware for 2-3 years unless there is something so good about the design that people will play it anyway.<P>There was advance warning that the switch to DirectX 7 would occur and DirectX 7 has been out for almost a year so it is probably not an unreasonable upgrade.  Personally, I can play a rpg 5-8 months before getting bored with it, so if EQ lasts longer before upgrades make it impossible to play, it was a good deal - besides, I need an excuse to buy a new computer - LOL<P>my 2cp
