<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Lets try not to get off the original topic. I believe the original question was to what extent is a company allowed to change the system requirements for a game that has already been released. And how often should they be alowed to do it. Obviously verant started with an out of date engine. In a way that has helped them because the more powerfull machines that we now have can process those simple polygon textures faster, easier and including a lot more polygons. A more current and agressive engine AND THE GRAPHICHS THAT THE CONSUMER BASE WOULD EXPECT TO SEE FOR THAT ENGINE might have had issues with more than a few mobs and players within the same vicinity.<P>Let me pose a diferent question:<BR>If verant had said: "The following servers will support direct X7.0 and the others will not. Please abandon your characters and move to a server appropriate to the level of your machine." Would that have been acceptable? Or is "The new server XYZ will be left with the old direct X 5.* standard. players from any server not capable of upgrading may request a move log." better?<P>Its all a question of what will alienate your customer base least. Forcing them to spend money to upgrade a system they finaly have working perfectly (upgrades are always tricky) or keeping them playing with an obsolete engine.<P>Given that the engine was state of the art when VI started developing the game and was nearly obsolete by the time the game was released can we expect everyone to want to play with the same old engine or is the majority of the PAYING consumer base willing to accept changes in requirements over the next 4 years or so this game will be in service?<P>Ooops, I've started rambling, sorry
</FONT>
