Well, you also have to consider that computer technology is advancing at a staggering rate.  The turn around for new tech is roughly 6 months, so basically every 6 months what you have in you're computer has just become obsolete.  Since EQ is a persistant, long term game, they have to make allowances to keep up with technology, otherwise people may just go elsewhere to play a different, more current game.  Also, it can be prohibitvely expensive to upgrade a computer, espically if you can't do it yourself.  If you can do it yourself, I would recommend doing it one piece at a time, if you can't afford to do one big upgrade.  Always start with CPU, then move on to either video card or memory, whichever is hurting more  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif">  Everything after that is really just for convience.  I know that I used an old SB 16 for over 3 years, and I never had a problem or was lacking for sound quality.
