After reading your post I went to the "official" EQ site and got the stated minimum specs.<P>- Windows 95 or Windows 98 <BR>- Pentium 166 (Note older Model Cyrix           processors WILL NOT WORK with EverQuest.) <BR>- 32 megabytes RAM <BR>- 28.8 Internet connection<BR>- Direct3D or Glide compliant videocard<BR>  w/ 4MB RAM <BR>- Sound Blaster compatible soundcard <BR>- Microsoft compatible mouse <BR>- 8x CD-ROM drive<P>Now I know that most people are not made of money but, lets face it, those specs now represent a pretty old PC.  Four years at the least I would guess and probably more.<P>I used to love Space Invaders (dating himself).  That was so cool.  But times change and it looks pretty sorry now.  Can't beleive I spent hours doing that!  The moral is, games have to keep up.  Gamers have to keep up too.  I loved Doom, and HAD to buy a new PC so I could play Quake.  We have a computer technology based hobby.  That means periodic upgrades.  My 2cp.<P>Just an aside: I LOVE your web site.  This is probably the single most useful EQ resource on the web.  Thank you.  Perhaps your many fans should take up a collection to get you a decent PC.
