<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The prime ingrediate is a playable game that people are willing to pay to particpate in. You can do that with the current technology.<BR>Quite frankly it can be done with technology that is 10years old. Because it is the people that make the game not the programing. The programing is only important for creating the framework that allows the people to participate in the game. If the game is designed with the people in mind the programing is only the means to the end.<P>Unfortunately, marketing begins to play a role in game design when investors see that they can generate a return on investment with a game. Then competition causes the designers to add more bells and whistles in order to attract more players which can turn a profit for the investors because more people are attracted to this game or that.(it's easier to add bells and whistles than to add content quailty) And the investor becomes the ultimate designing force behind any successful game. Therefore, we find ourselves with equipment that is not compatible with the latest updates in programing.
</FONT>
