<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Not trying to sound like a smug little s**t. But every one keeps saying NEW system. You "need to buy a new system to play".<BR>Where is that? I don't see that. What I see is a 50 dollar video card. Maybe a 60 dollar overdrive.<BR>I'm running a Generic Yamaha 3D sound card. (12 bucks)<BR>400 Celeron (under 50 bucks)<BR>96 Megs of ram (70 bucks or less now)<BR>You don't need a NEW system. just some simple upgrades to your existing one. And if your machine is a bit older then most there are ways to get old hardware components out there for it to help it play EQ.<BR>Also just a little FYI. Look at all the games slated to come out at the end of 2001 and early 2002. ALL are requiring 128 Megs of ram as minimum system requirements.<BR>More CPU Speed. Something like a 500 or better.<BR>Whether we like it or not we do have to keep up with advancing technology. It sucks I know. But if we didn't keep up we wouldn't have games like EQ.  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Tarkis
